<p>

<image location="right" width="250px" src="2007-Saturn-Outlook-XE.jpg" type="thumb">
<caption>

2007 Saturn Outlook XE
</caption>
</image>

The <b>Saturn Outlook</b> is a premium full-size <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../025/912025.xml">
crossover SUV</link> which debuted at the <fundamental_quantity wordnetid="113575869" confidence="0.8">
<time_period wordnetid="115113229" confidence="0.8">
<diversion wordnetid="100426928" confidence="0.8">
<event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<show wordnetid="100520257" confidence="0.8">
<festival wordnetid="115162388" confidence="0.8">
<act wordnetid="100030358" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<entertainment wordnetid="100429048" confidence="0.8">
<activity wordnetid="100407535" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../831/1479831.xml">
New York International Auto Show</link></activity>
</entertainment>
</psychological_feature>
</act>
</festival>
</show>
</event>
</diversion>
</time_period>
</fundamental_quantity>
.  The Outlook is based on the new <platform wordnetid="103961939" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../665/1172665.xml">
GM Lambda platform</link></platform>
, which it shares with the <car wordnetid="102958343" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../900/3405900.xml">
Buick Enclave</link></car>
, <car wordnetid="102958343" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../238/11507238.xml">
Chevrolet Traverse</link></car>
 and <car wordnetid="102958343" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../510/3225510.xml">
GMC Acadia</link></car>
.  The Outlook features the lowest sticker price among GM's Lambda crossover SUVs.</p>

<sec>
<st>
Driveline</st>
<p>

The Outlook is powered by the 3.6 L <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../665/4116665.xml">
V6</link> <link>
DOHC</link> <structure wordnetid="105225602" confidence="0.8">
<valve wordnetid="105395286" confidence="0.8">
<part wordnetid="109385911" confidence="0.8">
<body_part wordnetid="105220461" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../545/1127545.xml">
24-valve</link></body_part>
</part>
</valve>
</structure>
 <automobile_engine wordnetid="102761557" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../456/895456.xml">
HFV6 engine</link></automobile_engine>
 with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../704/845704.xml">
Variable Valve Timing</link>, available in two versions:
<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <b>XE</b> - 270 hp (198 kW) and 248 ft·lbf (331 Nm) of torque</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <b>XR</b> - 275 hp (199 kW) and 251 ft·lbf (335 Nm) of torque <it>(dual exhaust)''</it></entry>
</list>

Both versions use the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../984/1458984.xml">
Hydra-Matic</link> 6T75 six-speed <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../940/334940.xml">
automatic transmission</link>, and are available with either <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../078/755078.xml">
front-wheel drive</link> or <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../649/444649.xml">
all-wheel drive</link>.</p>

